# Native (Android / iOS)

- Keep native changes minimal; prefer Flutter plugins (`permission_handler`, etc.).
- Platform permissions must be declared in `AndroidManifest.xml` and `Info.plist`.
- Do not commit secrets, keystores, or `local.properties` API keys.
- Use flavors/schemes for dev, staging, and production env alignment.
- Health sync and device APIs require explicit permission flows with user rationale.
- After native dependency changes, run `flutter clean` and rebuild both platforms.

| Concern | Android | iOS |
|---------|---------|-----|
| Permissions | `AndroidManifest.xml` | `Info.plist` |
| Min SDK | `android/app/build.gradle.kts` | `ios/Podfile` |
| App ID | `applicationId` | `PRODUCT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER` |
